* Editor's note: This article is updated each time new information becomes available. JOHANNESBURG - A much-anticipated briefing on plans to rescue the economy, has been postponed.Finance Minister Malusi Gigaba was due to brief the media at midday.Instead, he'll be meeting with the ANC's leadership. And on Tuesday he'll hold talks with government's economic cluster.The plan is to develop a comprehensive response to the country's economic woes.This comes after ratings agency Moody s downgraded the country one notch to BAA3 -- one notch above sub-investment grade.READ: Recovery uncertain after SA dips into recessionOther ratings agency had already put South Africa in a sub-investment grade. The latest GDP figures show that the country has entered a technical recession.Cabinet has said that any interventions will be within current budget frameworks.eNCA